        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You’re an up-and-coming street artist, until one day, a Toreador patron discovered your work in a back alley while you were trying to ditch your spray paint cans. After that you became his blood doll while he funded your work and made sure the police didn’t bother you too much. As your talent grew, he decided to make you look cool in order to preserve your art for posterity. During salons and select court meetings your art was showed off by your patrons. At these meetings and gatherings of the Kindred or those of the blood, you learned many legends and lore of the kindred. These legends started to show up in your art and as a precaution, your sire embraced you as to give you incentive to be more careful with your work. He bided his time, waiting for the right moment to present you to the court. Now is the time for your release and it is up to you to keep performing and also to keep the Masquerade.\n\nNYC is the haven of the urban art seen, but it's also dangerous. It's only been a Camarilla city since 2000, and there's no one really in charge there. Besides, there is some AMAZING street art in LA, you've seen and heard about it. With your sire's leave, you've come here to see what there is to be seen, to be inspired, and to leave your mark. Banksy? Banksy who?"
        ],
        [
